{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CreatingNewUnits","doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UsingCustomCodeGeneration","doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CreatingCompositeUnits","doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/ConvertingBetweenCategories"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"GUUnitsGeneratorConversions"}],"title":"Getting Started","role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The target is broken up into 3 key subdirectories:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"units","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"source_generation","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"test_generation","type":"codeVoice"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We will examine each of these subdirectories in the following sections. For a quick guide explaining how to create a new unit,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"see the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"creatingnewunits"},{"text":" document.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Units","anchor":"Units","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"units","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" subdirectory is the simplist of all the other subdirectories. This folder contains the category definitions for each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unit type. A category is simply a group of units that describe\/measure the same phenomenon. For example, consider the "},{"code":"Distance","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"category which contains the units "},{"code":"metres","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"centimetres","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"millimetres","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This category is defined in "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/DistanceUnits"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"All categories must conform to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol to allow source and test generation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition to the units definitions, this subdirectory also contains the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" primitive types that are supported"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GUUnits"},{"type":"text","text":". You may view the supported C types in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/NumericTypes"},{"type":"text","text":", and the supported "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" types in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/SwiftNumericTypes"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"All units can be converted to\/from these supported primitive types."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lastly, it is worth mentioning that each unit type (e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres"},{"type":"text","text":" in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Distance"},{"type":"text","text":" category) has 4 different underlying types that support"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"varying levels of precision. These types are the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":" primitive types "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"double"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"float"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"uint64_t"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"int64_t"},{"type":"text","text":". Each unit is therefore"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"represented as a new type depending on it’s precision and is suffixed with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_d"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_f"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_u"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_t"},{"type":"text","text":" for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"double"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"float"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unit64_t"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"int64_t"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively in the source code. For example, consider the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres"},{"type":"text","text":" unit; in the generated "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":" source code, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unit is represented as 4 "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":" types: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres_d"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres_f"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres_u"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"metres_t"},{"type":"text","text":". The different versions of the unit type is referred"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to in this documentation as a units "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sign"},{"type":"text","text":", and is defined in the enum "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Signs"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Source Generation","anchor":"Source-Generation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This subdirectory contains the code required to generate the ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" sources for all of the units and their conversions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In order to generate the correct sources for each unit, an equivalent ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/FunctionBodyCreator"},{"text":" must be used for that unit type.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Simple types using ","type":"text"},{"code":"SI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" prefixes can utilise the existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GradualFunctionCreator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which performs simple multiplication or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"division with a pre-defined scale factor (see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Creating New Units","identifier":"creatingnewunits","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Creating New Units","type":"text"}]},{"text":"). If any unit performs conversions that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cannot be defined as a simple multiplication or divide, then a custom ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/FunctionBodyCreator"},{"text":" must be defined that implements","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" code to perform the conversion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To keep consistency between all unit categories, the definitions of the functions in ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will follow a naming convention that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is enforced by ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CFunctionDefinitionCreator","type":"reference"},{"text":". When used in tandem with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CompositeFunctionCreator","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/NumericTypeConverter","type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implementation is automatically created using the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/FunctionBodyCreator","type":"reference"},{"text":" of that unit. This process is completely","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automated and is not usually altered when adding new units. For convenience, all source generation is performed through","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsGenerator","type":"reference"},{"text":" that combines these types. For brevity, a new unit typically creates an extension on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsGenerator","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and a ","type":"text"},{"code":"typealias","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to allow easy initialisation (see ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating New Units"}],"isActive":true,"identifier":"creatingnewunits","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Creating New Units"},{"text":"). This process is demonstrated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TemperatureUnits","type":"reference"},{"text":" category below.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/\/ TemperatureUnits initialiser for C conversions.","extension UnitsGenerator where","    Creator == CompositeFunctionCreator<","        TemperatureFunctionCreator,","        CFunctionDefinitionCreator<TemperatureUnits>,","        NumericTypeConverter","    > {","","    \/\/\/ Initialise using TemperatureUnits and C conversions.","    \/\/\/ - Parameters:","    \/\/\/   - bodyCreator: The creator which generates function bodies.","    \/\/\/   - definitionCreator: The definitionCreate which generates function definitions.","    \/\/\/   - numericConverter: The numericConverter which generates numeric type conversions.","    \/\/\/   - helpers: The helpers which generate function names and some definitions.","    public init(","        bodyCreator: TemperatureFunctionCreator = TemperatureFunctionCreator(),","        definitionCreator: CFunctionDefinitionCreator<TemperatureUnits> = CFunctionDefinitionCreator(),","        numericConverter: NumericTypeConverter = NumericTypeConverter(),","        helpers: FunctionHelpers<Creator.Unit> = FunctionHelpers<Creator.Unit>()","    ) {","        self.init(creator: CompositeFunctionCreator(","            bodyCreator: bodyCreator,","            definitionCreator: definitionCreator,","            numericConverter: numericConverter","        ))","    }","","}","","\/\/\/ Temperature Units Generator","public typealias TemperatureUnitsGenerator = UnitsGenerator<","    CompositeFunctionCreator<","        TemperatureFunctionCreator,","        CFunctionDefinitionCreator<TemperatureUnits>,","        NumericTypeConverter","    >",">"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The top level code may then create a source generator for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Temperature"},{"type":"text","text":" by invoking:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let generator = TemperatureUnitsGenerator()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"Test Generation","anchor":"Test-Generation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This package also generates tests for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" sources. All of the code that handles the test generation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is contained within the ","type":"text"},{"code":"test_generation","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" folder. A test in this package is represented as an input to output relationship.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Given some input, the test will perform a function with that input and assert that the output from the function matches the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"expected output. This relationship is defined inside a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestGenerator","type":"reference"},{"text":" that creates arrays of input to output relationships","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(using ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestParameters","type":"reference"},{"text":") for a given conversion function.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple types using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SI"},{"type":"text","text":" prefixes may use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GradualTestGenerator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to generate the tests for them. Custom unit types or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"those that cannot use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GradualFunctionCreator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to implement their conversion function must create a custom type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that conforms to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestGenerator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The default implementation of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestGenerator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will provide the test cases"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the numeric conversions, i.e conversions containing the types defined in "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/NumericTypes","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The custom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestGenerator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will only need to provide the tests for a unit to unit conversion."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Public Interface","anchor":"Public-Interface","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The entire public interface to this target is encapsulated within ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GUUnitsGenerator"},{"text":". This struct provides methods","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for generating sources and tests for the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift"},{"text":" targets of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GUUnits"},{"text":" package. The respective methods","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in this struct will use the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsGenerator"},{"text":" for souce generation, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitProtocol"},{"text":" for unit definition,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestGenerator"},{"text":" for test generation following the procedures outlined above. An example of this entire process","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is shown in ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Creating New Units","type":"text"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Creating New Units","identifier":"creatingnewunits"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GUUnitsGeneratorConversions"},{"type":"text","text":" is the main target of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"guunits_generator"},{"type":"text","text":". This target provides the unit and category"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"definitions for all the code generated in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GUUnits"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/GUUnitsGenerator":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GUUnitsGenerator"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create the source files the C and swift targets of guunits."}],"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/guunitsgenerator","title":"GUUnitsGenerator","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GUUnitsGenerator","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GUUnitsGenerator"}]},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/CreatingNewUnits":{"abstract":[{"text":"Provides a guide and example for creating new units.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CreatingNewUnits","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/creatingnewunits","title":"Creating New Units"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/UnitProtocol":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UnitProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitProtocol","title":"UnitProtocol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A protocol for representing unit types that exist within a unit category."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A unit category represents a type of data that can be expressed with different"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"units. Examples include Distance, Time, Angles, etc. Conforming types might","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"contain many units for a category, e.g. Distance can have metres, centimetres,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"millimetres, etc.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnitProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/unitprotocol","type":"topic"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/GradualTestGenerator":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","title":"GradualTestGenerator","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Struct used to generate test parameters for units that are convertable using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constant factors. e.g. 10 millimetres in a centimetre."}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GradualTestGenerator","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/gradualtestgenerator","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GradualTestGenerator","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GradualTestGenerator","kind":"identifier"}]},"creatingnewunits":{"identifier":"creatingnewunits","title":"Creating New Units","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Creating New Units","type":"text"}],"url":"creatingnewunits"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/NumericTypes":{"title":"NumericTypes","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NumericTypes","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NumericTypes","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The numeric types supported by guunits."}],"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/numerictypes","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/NumericTypes","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/DistanceUnits":{"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/distanceunits","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Unit for representing distances."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DistanceUnits"}],"title":"DistanceUnits","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/DistanceUnits","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DistanceUnits"}]},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/GradualFunctionCreator":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GradualFunctionCreator","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GradualFunctionCreator","title":"GradualFunctionCreator","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A function body creator that converts between different units by scaling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the magnitude of one unit by a constant value. Examples of this type of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behaviour is seen in SI units where kilo is 1000 times smaller than the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Mega prefix.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GradualFunctionCreator","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/gradualfunctioncreator","type":"topic"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/ConvertingBetweenCategories":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This guide provides instructions for creating relations between different unit categories. A user may use a relation to convert a unit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into another unit from a different category."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"article","title":"Coverting Between Categories","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/convertingbetweencategories","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/ConvertingBetweenCategories"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A target for generating the GUUnits package."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions","title":"GUUnitsGeneratorConversions","role":"collection"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/UnitsGenerator":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/unitsgenerator","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnitsGenerator"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsGenerator","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnitsGenerator"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Struct that generates the code for all the possible conversion functions.","type":"text"}],"title":"UnitsGenerator"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/TemperatureUnits":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TemperatureUnits"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Category for temperature units."}],"title":"TemperatureUnits","type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TemperatureUnits","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/temperatureunits","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TemperatureUnits"}]},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/Signs":{"title":"Signs","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Signs","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Signs","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Enum containing the standard guunits signs."}],"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/signs","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Signs","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/TestParameters":{"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/testparameters","title":"TestParameters","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TestParameters"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Class for storing expected test result from an input."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TestParameters","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TestParameters"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/SwiftNumericTypes":{"url":"\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/swiftnumerictypes","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SwiftNumericTypes"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type containing Swift-supported types for guunits."}],"title":"SwiftNumericTypes","navigatorTitle"